---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
import HitCounter from '../components/HitCounter.astro';
---

<Page title="alexander campos" description="Hand-built personal site. building things to protect how we think.">
  <section class="splash">
    <p class="tagline">building things to protect how we think.</p>

    <div class="retro-marquee-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="retro-marquee-text">
        last updated march 2026 — yes this was a marquee tag — it got promoted — it's css now — still slow on purpose&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;last updated march 2026 — yes this was a marquee tag — it got promoted — it's css now — still slow on purpose
      </span>
    </div>

    <div class="intro">
      <p>
        I'm Alex. I work in regulated finance during the day and build local intelligence
        infrastructure in between. I'm also starting to <a href="/writing">write about it</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        I noticed how language reframes the way someone sees themselves -- whether
        it comes from a person or a model, the effect is the same. That observation
        became <a href="/projects/guardian">Guardian</a>. The deeper problem it
        surfaced became <a href="/projects/forgeframe">ForgeFrame</a> --
        infrastructure for keeping what's yours on your machine.
        <a href="https://reframed.works">Reframed</a> is the first product.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is hand-built with a mix of agentic engineering, intuition,
        and the kind of judgment that only comes from knowing what the tool
        can't decide for you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <nav class="enter-nav" aria-label="Quick links">
      <a href="/projects" class="enter-link">projects >></a>
      <a href="/about" class="enter-link">about me >></a>
      <a href="/writing" class="enter-link">writing >></a>
    </nav>

    <p class="cta-line">
      Operations background. Self-taught engineer. Currently building AI infrastructure.
      <a href="/resume">See the resume</a> or <a href="mailto:adc.acampos@gmail.com">get in touch</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="counter-row">
      <HitCounter />
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c you are at the front door. ',
      'color: #b8965a; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>

  <script is:inline src="/islands/hit-counter.js"></script>
</Page>

<style>
  .splash {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--white-60);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .intro p {
    color: var(--glow);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .enter-nav {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .enter-link {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--gold-accent);
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .enter-link:hover {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
    border-bottom: none;
    transition: none;
  }

  .cta-line {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cta-line a {
    color: var(--gold-accent);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold-accent);
  }

  .counter-row {
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--white-08);
  }

  /* ── Pixel Grid Hover Texture ── */
  @media (hover: hover) {
    .enter-link:hover {
      background-image: url("data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg width='2' height='2' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Crect width='1' height='1' fill='white' fill-opacity='0.04'/%3E%3C/svg%3E");
      background-size: 2px 2px;
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
